- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also likely as the paper describes the development of a publicly available tool. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of semantic information about places. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is relevant as the paper discusses the implications of using location-based data for urban planning and mobile recommendation scenarios. 
- cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences) is also relevant as the paper deals with social networks and urban spaces.
